1 B. For purposes of this Section, the following definitions apply:
2 (1) "Aerospace flight activities" mean any act or activity related to the
3 research, development, testing, manufacture, preparation, launch, operation, reentry,
4 descent, landing, or post-landing recovery of an aeronautic or astronautic launch
5 vehicle, craft, payload, or related equipment, including but not limited to, fueling,
6 integration, conditioning, and transporting, including but not limited to the transport
7 of goods or persons, and any associated ground support operations whether
8 conducted on-site or involving overflight.
9 (2) "Aerospace flight entity" means any person, corporation, partnership,
10 limited liability company, or any other entity that conducts aerospace flight activities
11 and, to the extent required by federal law, holds or operates anywhere under a valid
12 Federal Aviation Administration license, experimental permit, or other authorization
13 for the relevant activities requiring such a license. This also includes any employee,
14 officer, director, agent, contractor, manufacturer, supplier, or vendor of such entity,
15 any owner or lessor of immovable property used for aerospace flight activities, and
16 any political subdivision or public entity with a contractual or operational
17 relationship facilitating such activities.
18 C.(1) A cause of action against an aerospace flight entity arising from any
19 act of the aerospace flight entity in connection with a public issue shall be subject to
20 a special motion to strike, unless the court determines that the plaintiff has
21 established a probability of success on the claim.
22 (2) In making its determination, the court shall consider the pleadings and
23 supporting and opposing affidavits stating the facts upon which the liability or
24 defense is based.
25 (3) If the court determines that the plaintiff has established a probability of
26 success on the claim, that determination shall be admissible in evidence at any later
27 stage of the proceeding.
28 D. In any action subject to Subsection C of this Section, a prevailing party
29 on a special motion to strike shall be awarded reasonable attorney fees and costs.
